---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms governing use of tackyturquoise.com and purchases."
>
  <section class="policy">
    <div class="policy__inner">
      <div class="policy__crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> &nbsp;/&nbsp; Terms of Service</div>

      <h1>Terms of <em>Service.</em></h1>
      <p class="policy__updated">Last updated: 4/25/2026</p>

      <p class="policy__lede">
        Welcome to Tacky Turquoise. These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of
        tackyturquoise.com (the "Site") and any purchases made through it. By using the
        Site or placing an order, you agree to these Terms.
      </p>

      <p>
        Tacky Turquoise is a trade name of Apex Quality Analytics LLC, a Colorado
        limited liability company ("we," "us," "our").
      </p>

      <h2>1. Eligibility</h2>
      <p>
        You must be at least 18 years old to make a purchase. By placing an order, you
        represent that you meet this requirement.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Products</h2>
      <p>We sell handmade, one-of-a-kind turquoise jewelry. Because each piece is unique:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Once a piece is sold, it is no longer available</li>
        <li>Photos represent the actual piece you'll receive, but slight variations in color or pattern may appear due to monitor settings or natural stone variation</li>
        <li>We do not produce duplicates of sold pieces</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to limit quantities, refuse service, correct pricing errors,
        and cancel orders affected by such errors at any time, including after an order
        has been submitted.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Pricing and Payment</h2>
      <p>
        All prices are listed in US Dollars and are exclusive of applicable sales tax,
        which will be calculated at checkout. We accept payment through Stripe, which
        processes credit and debit card transactions on our behalf. By submitting payment
        information, you authorize us to charge the total amount shown at checkout.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Order Acceptance</h2>
      <p>
        Submitting an order is an offer to purchase, not a guarantee of acceptance. We
        may decline or cancel any order, and will refund any payment in full if we do so.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Shipping</h2>
      <p>
        US shipping only at this time. See our <a href="/shipping">Shipping Policy</a>
        for full details.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Returns and Refunds</h2>
      <p>
        All sales are final. We accept returns only when a piece arrives damaged in
        shipping. See our <a href="/refunds">Refund Policy</a> for full details.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on the Site — including product photography, descriptions, the
        Tacky Turquoise name and branding — is owned by Apex Quality Analytics LLC. You
        may not reproduce, distribute, or use this content for commercial purposes without
        written permission.
      </p>

      <h2>8. User Conduct</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the Site for any unlawful purpose</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any part of the Site, our servers, or our backend systems</li>
        <li>Interfere with the Site's security features or normal operation</li>
        <li>Use automated tools (bots, scrapers) to access or copy the Site</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and our products are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind,
        express or implied, except where prohibited by law. We do not warrant that the
        Site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each piece is handmade, which means small variations in stone, bead size, and
        finish are part of its character and not defects.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, our total liability for any claim arising
        from these Terms or your use of the Site is limited to the amount you paid for
        the affected order. We are not liable for indirect, incidental, consequential,
        or punitive damages.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Governing Law and Disputes</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Colorado, without regard to
        its conflict-of-law principles. Any dispute arising under these Terms will be
        resolved in the state or federal courts located in Montrose County, Colorado, and
        you consent to the personal jurisdiction of those courts.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms at any time. The "Last updated" date at the top
        reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after changes
        constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Email us at
        <a href="mailto:orders@tackyturquoise.com">orders@tackyturquoise.com</a>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <p class="policy__signoff">
        <strong>Apex Quality Analytics LLC</strong>
        DBA Tacky Turquoise<br />
        Olathe, Colorado
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</Base>
